x4freetext: data from 16O+184W reaction were
compiled at EXFOR Entry D6049
Evaporation residue were detected at the focal
plane of HIRA using a 50 x 50 mm**2 2D position
sensitive silicon detector with a resistive layer at
the front.
Elastically scattered beam-like particles
were registered in two silicon surface barrier
detectors.
A 14 element BGO detector array was mounted at
the target chamber for measuring gamma fold
distribution in coincidence with ERs at the focal
plane.
Enriched isotopic (99.99 %) 181-Ta (250 mu-m/cm2)
target on carbon backing was used for the measurement.
ERs were separated using the recoil mass
spectrometer. Transmission efficiency of HIRA was
determined by the gamma ray method in separate run.
